# UI Language — English Only

All **user-facing system text** must be **English** for consistency across the CMS.

## Applies to

- Page titles, subtitles, descriptions
- Navigation labels (`config/nav.ts`, sidebar, tabs)
- Buttons, links, placeholders, tooltips
- Table headers, filter labels, pagination text
- Empty states, success/error messages, confirmations
- Form labels, validation messages (`lib/validations/`)
- `aria-label`, `aria-description`, `title` attributes
- Status/badge labels and enum display text
- Settings / Appearance drawer copy

## Does NOT apply to

- **Article content** (title, excerpt, body) — author-controlled
- **Git commits, PRs, code comments** — follow team preference
- **User chat** with the agent — respond in the user's language

## Locale

- UI strings: English
- Date/time display: `en-US` (e.g. `Intl.DateTimeFormat("en-US", …)`)
- Keep copy short, neutral, product-tone — like macOS System Settings

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<Button>Buat Artikel</Button>
<p>Belum ada artikel</p>
aria-label="Cari artikel"

// ✅ GOOD
<Button>Create Article</Button>
<p>No articles yet</p>
aria-label="Search articles"
```

```ts
// ❌ BAD
{ id: "draft", label: "Draft" } // mixed — nav in Indonesian elsewhere
export const statusLabels = { draft: "Draf", published: "Terbit" }

// ✅ GOOD
{ title: "Articles", href: "/articles" }
export const statusLabels = { draft: "Draft", published: "Published" }
```

## When editing existing UI

Replace Indonesian (or mixed) strings with English in the same change — do not add new non-English system copy.
